ons of doctrine explicit, revealing how they work, and how they shape the law that emerges. How to Do Things with Legal Doctrine will help all those studying or working with law to gain a more systematic understanding of the doctrinal moves many of our best lawyers make intuitively.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aJurisprudence. 0aLawxMethodology. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh  abaselines.  aformalism.  aframing.  alegal analysis.  alegal reasoning.  apurposivism.  arealism.  arhetoric.  arules and standards.  atextualism.1 aGriffin, Amy J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishz978311070486008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020z9783110704587oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831106930960 cprintz978022672610640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226726380423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226726380/original  a978-3-11-069309-6  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070486-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020